# Functional C++ on Windows

This is a collection of simple toy counter programs which demonstrate the implementation of some functional
style programming in C++ on Windows (WinUI3) using the [immer](https://github.com/arximboldi/immer) and [lager](https://github.com/arximboldi/lager) libraries.

## Dependencies

These projects are contained in a Visual Studio 2022 solution and require the [immer](https://github.com/arximboldi/immer) and [lager](https://github.com/arximboldi/lager)
header only library locations to be added to the INCLUDE environment variable.

